As one of South Africa’s largest independent private higher education institutions, Eduvos prides itself in preparing its graduates for the reality of the working world. Their campuses of the future, industry relevant qualifications and expert academic staff make for a personalised learning experience where students matter – and can flourish. “We are so proud of each and every one of our talented graduates at Eduvos. We have no doubt that they will make a meaningful contribution to organisations and society as they assist us in our mission to shape Africa’s potential and prosperity. The executive team, campus managers and all our staff, are honoured to have been a part of their learning journey; and are delighted to be celebrating their special graduation day with them and their families.” said Siegie Brownlee, Eduvos executive director. The graduation ceremonies will be held between 22 April and 13 May 2022. There will be over 1,720 graduates taking to the stage to receive 1,254 degrees, 434 higher certificates, and 39 honours degrees.To learn more about Eduvos, its 12 campuses nationwide and their accredited qualifications, visit eduvos.com.